# Vercel Speed Insights Implementation

Successfully installed and configured Vercel Speed Insights for this Next.js 14 project.

## Changes Made

### 1. Package Installation
- Installed `@vercel/speed-insights@^2.0.0` package using npm
- Updated `package.json` with the new dependency
- Updated `package-lock.json` with dependency resolution

### 2. Code Configuration
Modified `app/layout.tsx`:
- Added import: `import { SpeedInsights } from '@vercel/speed-insights/next'`
- Added `<SpeedInsights />` component to the end of the body section

## Implementation Details

Following the official Vercel Speed Insights documentation from https://vercel.com/docs/speed-insights/quickstart, I implemented the framework-specific instructions for Next.js 13.5+:

1. **Package**: Used the Next.js-specific import path `@vercel/speed-insights/next`
2. **Placement**: Added the SpeedInsights component at the end of the `<body>` tag in the root layout
3. **Compatibility**: Preserved all existing code including Google Analytics integration
4. **Code Style**: Maintained the existing formatting and structure of the layout file

## Verification

✅ Build completed successfully (`npm run build`)
✅ No TypeScript errors
✅ No linting errors
✅ Existing functionality preserved (Google Analytics, metadata, etc.)

## Next Steps

After deployment to Vercel:
1. Enable Speed Insights in the Vercel dashboard for this project
2. The component will automatically start collecting performance metrics
3. View the data in the Speed Insights section of the Vercel dashboard

